quran[23]{c,v,t,f}:
  51,52,"Likewise, no messenger came to those before them without being told: “A magician, or a madman!”",""
  51,53,"Did they suggest this to one another<sup>17</sup>? Rather they are transgressing people.","[17] i.e., Did the previous disbelievers pass on these false allegations to the pagans of Makkah so they repeat their words?"
  51,54,"So turn away from them [O Prophet], for you are not to blame<sup>18</sup>.","[18] After you have delivered the message."
  51,55,"But keep reminding them, for reminder benefits the believers.",""
  51,56,"I have not created the jinn and mankind except to worship Me.",""
  51,57,"I seek no provision from them, nor do I want them to feed Me.",""
  51,58,"Indeed, it is Allah Who is the All-Provider<sup>19</sup>, Lord of Power, the Mighty.","[19] He Provides His creatures with everything they need. Among His provisions is guidance."
  51,59,"Indeed, those who do wrong will have a share [of punishment] like that of their predecessors, so let them not ask Me to hasten it.",""
  51,60,"So woe to those who disbelieve from [the punishment of] the Day which they are promised.",""
  52,1,"By the mount of Tūr<sup>1</sup>,","[1] Where Allah Almighty communicated with Moses (عليه السلام)."
  52,2,"and by the Book inscribed<sup>2</sup>","[2] i.e., the Qur’an."
  52,3,"on an unrolled parchment<sup>3</sup>,","[3] i.e., a spread-out scroll."
  52,4,"and by the much-frequented House<sup>4</sup>,","[4] Which is frequented by angels or the Ka‘bah in Makkah which is frequented by pilgrims."
  52,5,"and by the canopy raised high,",""
  52,6,"and by the sea set on fire<sup>5</sup>.","[5] On the Day of Resurrection, or ""by the overflowed sea."""
  52,7,"The punishment of your Lord will surely come to pass;",""
  52,8,"there is none who can avert it.",""
  52,9,"On the Day when the heaven will convulse violently<sup>6</sup>,","[6] The heavens will be shaken violently, indicating the occurrence of the Hour. The word ""maur"" originally means turning round, rotating, swinging, swaying, etc."
  52,10,"and the mountains will move a horrible movement<sup>7</sup>.","[7] They will turn into dust, moving as clouds."
  52,11,"Then woe to the deniers on that Day,",""
  52,12,"those who amuse themselves in falsehood.",""
  52,13,"On the Day when they will be shoved into the Fire forcefully,",""
  52,14,"[They will be told,] “This is the Fire which you used to deny.",""
